United States Consulate
Sierra Leone W.C. of Africa
March 18th 1876

Sir,
Requiring a temporary change of climate I beg to inform you that I intend soon to proceed to 
 <unclear/> for a few weeks residence there.

During my absence I have in charge of ths Office with the Archives etc. thereto belonging James Frame Esqre who was also my representant on the occasion of my former absence from my post. 

Trusting that you will approve of and <unclear/> my temporary leave.

I have the honor to be
Sir,
Your most obedient servant
M . Claudale
U.S. Consul

To the Honorable
The Secretary of State
Washington D.C.

